Daniel P. Faigin (faigin@aero.org) writes:

> I'm not sure that is a virus. First of all, if you set your permissions
> properly, then root programs cannot be modified (you are right, now all

Yes, they can - by root, or by bin, or by any other "user" with such
privileges. All you have to do is to fool such user to execute an
infected program. Or to fool somebody whom this user trusts to run an
infected program. Or to fool somebody whom this somebody trusts to run
an infected program. Or... Can you say "transitivity of the
information flow"?

Regards,
Vesselin
